<h5>Export Card Configuration</h5>	
<p>The export card option is a plugin that allows you to export the backlog tasks. This allows you to run workshops using the 
	current set of stories. It works using a configurable template written in a markup language called YAML.
	We will modify the suggested example from the authors by adding the subject to the card in the first row.
	<%= link_to 'web site',' https://github.com/finnlabs/openproject-pdf_export' %></p>	
<%= link_to image_tag("openproject/exportconfig1.png",:size => '450x500', alt: "user settings"  ), class: 'centre' %>
<p>Select "New Export Card Config" and paste the YAML code below into the page. Give your configuration a name and set number per page to 1.</p>
	
<pre>
group1:
  has_border: false
  height: 200
  rows:
group1:
  has_border: false
  height: 200
  rows:
    row1:
      height: 50
      priority: 1
      columns:
        id:
          has_label: false
          min_font_size: 10
          max_font_size: 20
          font_size: 20
          font_style: bold
          text_align: left
          minimum_lines: 2
          render_if_empty: false
          width: 10%
        subject:
          has_label: false
          font_size: 15
          font_style: italic
          minimum_lines: 2
          render_if_empty: false
          width: 50%
        due_date:
          has_label: false
          font_size: 15
          font_style: italic
          minimum_lines: 2
          render_if_empty: false
          width: 40%
    row2:
      priority: 2
      columns:
        status:
          has_label: true
          indented: true
          font_size: 15
          font_style: normal
          minimum_lines: 1
          render_if_empty: true
group2:
  has_border: true
  rows:
    row1:
      height: 80
      priority: 2
      columns:
        description:
          has_label: true
          indented: false
          font_size: 15
          font_style: normal
          minimum_lines: 1
          render_if_empty: true
    row2:
      priority: 2
      columns:
        status:
          has_label: true
          font_size: 15
          font_style: normal
          minimum_lines: 1
          render_if_empty: true
    row2:
      priority: 2
      columns:
        custom_field_name:
          has_label: true
          font_size: 15
          minimum_lines: 1
group3:
  rows:
    row1:
      priority: 2
      columns:
        children:
          has_label: true
          has_count: true
          indented: true
          font_size: 15
          font_style: normal
          minimum_lines: 1
          render_if_empty: true
</pre>



